# Project Overview
Jarosz Logistics is a static, multi-page marketing site for a Northwest Arkansas
small business offering three services: mobile auto detailing, smart-home
installs, and box-truck logistics. The site is hosted on a private VPS.

# Structure
- `index.html` — landing page; hero + three service cards (detailing, smart
  home, logistics) + contact.
- `detailing/index.html` — detailing service page with pricing tables and an
  embedded Cal.com booking calendar.
- `smart-home/index.html` — install service page with pricing and contact CTA.
- `logistics/index.html` — trucking/last-mile content.
- `assets/css/styles.css` — shared design system.
- `assets/js/main.js` — year stamping, smooth scroll, active nav highlight.

# Styling Notes
- CSS variables in `:root` define the color system. Per-page accent is set by
  a `body.page-*` class (`page-detail` amber, `page-smart` teal,
  `page-logistics` sky). Add new colors via variables, not hex literals.
- Layout uses flexbox and CSS grid. Mobile-first; the main breakpoints are
  700px (contact card), 800px (service grid), 900px (two-column grids).
- The dark theme uses radial gradients on `<body>` for ambient color; keep
  background changes consistent.
- Uses `color-mix()` for tinted backgrounds — requires modern browsers
  (Chrome 111+, Safari 16.2+, Firefox 113+). Provide rgba fallbacks if older
  browsers become a target.

# JavaScript Notes
- Vanilla JS only, loaded from `/assets/js/main.js` at the bottom of each page.
- The active nav state is derived from `<body data-page="...">`; matching
  `<a data-page="...">` entries in `nav.primary` receive `.active`.
- Smooth scroll hooks every `a[href^="#"]`; ensure new anchors use real IDs.

# Cal.com Booking
- The detailing page (`detailing/index.html#book`) embeds Cal.com inline.
- The embed uses placeholder `calLink: "jaroszlogistics/auto-detail"`.
  Before launch:
    1. Create a Cal.com account at https://cal.com using
       `julius@jaroszlogistics.com`.
    2. Create an event type "Auto Detail" (suggested 2h, 30m buffer, in-person
       at attendee location).
    3. Configure availability under Availability → Working Hours.
    4. Replace `jaroszlogistics/auto-detail` in the script block with the real
       Cal link (username/event-slug).
- Branding color (`cal-brand`) is set to amber `#fbbf24` to match the detailing
  accent.

# Testing / Preview
- Serve locally with e.g. `python3 -m http.server` from the project root
  (file:// will break the absolute `/assets/...` paths and Cal.com embed).
- Validate layout across mobile (<700px), tablet (~800px), and desktop.

# Accessibility
- Maintain ARIA labels on `<nav>` and section headings; `.sr-only` is available
  for visually-hidden labels.
- Keep `:focus-visible` outlines on `.btn` and `.cta`; don't strip them.

